      "content": "For your 4-year-old weighing 35 lbs, a safe dose of Tylenol (acetaminophen) is typically around 10-15 mg per kg of body weight, given every 4-6 hours as needed. First, convert your child's weight from pounds to kilograms: 35 lbs is approximately 15.9 kg. So, the dose should be around 159-239 mg every 4-6 hours.\n\nThe Tylenol infant drops are concentrated at 160 mg/5 ml. To find out how many ml to give, use the following calculation:\n\n159 mg / 160 mg = 0.993 ml\n239 mg / 160 mg = 1.494 ml\n\nSo, you should give your child approximately 1 to 1.5 ml of the Tylenol infant drops, ensuring not to exceed the recommended dosage for your child's weight. Always make sure to administer the correct dose and closely monitor them, and consult a healthcare professional as soon as possible.",
